{
  "texts": [
    "The quark sector is the same as in the SM:q i L are SU(2) L left-handed quark doublets, u i R, d i Rthe right-handed singlets, i = {1, 2, 3} is a generation index.",
    "In the lepton sector, ℓ i L denote the left-handed lepton doublets, ν i R and e i R the right-handed singlets.",
    "Before the electroweak SSB the Z ′ couplings to fermions are flavour conserving: for a generic fermion ψ the interaction Lagrangian with Z ′ readsL Z ′ int (ψ) = g Z ′ z ψ ψ γ µ ψ Z ′ µ,(1)with Z ′ µ the gauge boson field, g Z ′ the U(1) ′ gauge coupling and z ψ the z-hypercharge of ψ.",
    "Hence, in terms of left-and right-handed fields ψ L(R) the fermion-Z ′ interaction Lagrangian isL Z ′ int = i,j (∆ ψ L) ij ψi L γ µ ψ j L + (∆ ψ R) ij ψi R γ µ ψ j R Z ′ µ,(2)where(∆ ψ L(R)) ij = g Z ′ z ψ L(R) δ ij.",
    "(3)After the enlargement of the gauge group, the SM remains free of gauge anomalies imposing anomaly cancellation conditions."
  ]
}